Fix go:S1172 (unused param) on this handler.

go:S1172 internal/transport/handler.go:42 Remove the unused function parameter "w".

For context, the flagged code looks like:

// ServeHTTP satisfies http.Handler; w is unused because this handler only
// records the request for the audit pipeline and returns nothing to the client.
func (h *AuditHandler) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    h.recorder.Record(r)
}

The AuditHandler is registered via mux.Handle("/audit", auditHandler) and is also asserted with `var _ http.Handler = (*AuditHandler)(nil)`. Removing or renaming the parameter changes the method signature so it no longer satisfies http.Handler, and the build/tests break.
